 most popular girls' names in some parishes. It has always been particularly popular in Scotland and northern England (borne, for example, by  Grace Darling , the lighthouse keeper's daughter whose heroism in  1838 , saving sailors in a storm, caught the popular imagination). In more recent times it was famous as the name of the actress  Grace Kelly  (  1928–82 ), who became  Princess Grace  of Monaco. In Ireland it is used as an Anglicized form of   Gráinne   ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705207,"age":10,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705208,"age":12,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705212,"age":45,"year":"1620","julianDay":2312753,"title":"The Pilgrims Board the Mayflower","description":"\"The Pilgrims boarded the Mayflower in search of religious freedom in the New World in September 1620. The Mayflower set sail from Plymouth, England, with 102 passengers, 40 of whom called themselves \"\"Saints.\"\" After two stormy months at sea, the ship reached the New World. Nearly half of the group died during their first winter due to malnutrition and the harsh New England winter.\"","url":"https://www.themayflowersociety.org/the-pilgrims/pilgrim-history","urlTitle":"The Mayflower Society - Pilgrim History","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705213,"age":67,"year":"1642","toYear":"1651","julianDay":2320789,"title":"The English Civil War","description":"A series of conflicts regarding England's governance during the years 1642 to 1651 is now known as The English Civil War. Charles I summoned supporters to join him against his enemies in Parliament. In October 1642, nearly 10,000 men fought for Charles I and chased Parliament across the River Tamar. Fighting continued for years and was finally ended at the Battle of Worcester on September 3, 1651, with a Parliamentarian victory.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705216,"age":113,"year":"1688","toYear":"1689","julianDay":2337590,"title":"Glorious Revolution","description":"The Glorious Revolution brought the downfall of Catholic King James II and the reign of his Protestant daughter Mary and her Dutch husband, William III of Orange.","url":"http://www.bbc.co.uk/history/british/civil_war_revolution/glorious_revolution_01.shtml","urlTitle":"BBC - Glorious Revolution","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"When Grace was born on 12 March 1574, in England, her father, Thomas Bucke, was 29 and her mother, Anne Calvert, was 29. She married Robert Porter in 1590, in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"12 March, 1566–":"12. märts 1574–Surnud","1567–1665":"1567–1665","1570–Female":"1570–Surnud","1574–Female":"1574–Surnud","1561–1590":"1561–1590","1565–1612":"1565–1612","1591–1662":"1591–1662","1592–Male":"1592–Surnud","1545–1603":"1545–1603","1545–Female":"1545–Surnud","1561":"1561","1592":"1592","1570":"1570","1591":"1591","1590":"1590","1 January 1565":"1. jaanuar 1565","1689":"1689","1612":"1612","1688":"1688","1545":"1545","1567":"1567","1665":"1665","1642":"1642","1620":"1620","1587":"1587","1565":"1565","1651":"1651","1585":"1585","1662":"1662","1574":"1574","12 March, 1566":"12. märts 1574","1603":"1603","Layston, Hertfordshire, England":"Layston, Hertfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England":"